<HEADLINE> Pakistan Announces 30 Pct Cut in Electricity Bills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif Sunday announced a 50 percent cut in electricity's
additional surcharge to bring down the bills by 30 percent in a
move to provide relief to the people.
</P>
<P>
In a televised address to the nation, Sharif said he would not
surrender to problems faced by his government and the people and
was determined to beat them with the blessings of God and prayers
of the masses.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the 15th Constitutional Amendment Bill passed
Friday by the National Assembly, Sharif said that by protecting
the democratic institutions, his government was taking steps to
make the country a model Islamic welfare state where the
minorities will live freely and "there is a respect for women and
doors are open for economic development."
</P>
<P>
Sharif also said the nuclear blasts conducted by Pakistan in
May were necessary for the survival, honor and glory of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
