<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Release 10 Iranian Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
Sunday released 10 more Iranian prisoners on the occasion of the
visit by Muhammad Khader, special envoy of Palestinian President
Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Khader, who Saturday visited Pakistan and met Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif, visited the Taliban's headquarters of Kandahar and
met Taliban supreme leader Mohammad Omar, according to informed
sources.
</P>
<P>
He delivered a special message to Omar from Arafat and told him
that the current border tension between Iran and Afghanistan is
harmful not only for the peoples of the two countries but for the
whole Islamic world.
</P>
<P>
He also said any conflict between the Taliban and Iran would
affect the Palestinian cause.
</P>
<P>
The special envoy hoped that Iran and Taliban leaders would
show restraint and settle their dispute peacefully.
</P>
<P>
He thanked Omar for releasing 10 more Iranian prisoners and
said the step would help in reducing bitterness between Iran and
the Taliban.
</P>
<P>
Reiterating his support for the Palestinian cause, Omar said
the Taliban have no objection to releasing more Iranian prisoners
but would seek guarantee for the release of Taliban prisoners
under the opposition's custody.
</P>
<P>
The freed Iranian prisoners are likely to arrive in Islamabad
Monday in a special plane along with the Palestinian envoy.
</P>
</TEXT>
