<HEADLINE> Saudi King Congratulate Yemen on Recovering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabian King Fahd Bin
Abddullah Abdul-Aziz on Sunday congratulated Yemen on restoring
sovereignty over the Hanish archipelago.
</P>
<P>
This is the second friendly gesture from the Saudi royal family
in two days after the ruling of international arbitration on
Yemen's rights to sovereignty over the islands.
</P>
<P>
In a cable of congratulation to Yemeni President Ali Abdullah
Saleh, Saudi King Fahd Bin Abddullah Abdul-Aziz said "I hope the
decision of the International Arbitration Committee (IAC) would
enhance relations between Yemen and Eritrea and serve their common
interest," the Saudi Press Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The London-based IAC ruled Friday in favor of Yemen in its
dispute with Eritrea over the Red Sea Islands of Hanish.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday Crown Prince and Deputy Prime Minister Abdullah
Ibn Abdul-Aziz sent a similar congratulation from Hawaii of
the United States where he was spending a private vacation.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone call to President Saleh, Abdullah also
reviewed bilateral relations between Saudi Arabia and Yemen, and
the latest developments of Arab, regional and international
arenas.
</P>
<P>
The regional heavy-weight Saudi Arabia itself is also locked in
a territorial row with Yemen.
</P>
<P>
On July 19, a dispute over the Red Sea island of Duaima,
claimed by both Riyadh and Sanaa, led to an armed confrontation
between the two Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Since then, several rounds of high-level talks have been
held between Saudi Arabia and Yemen on ways to resolve the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have agreed to do their utmost to prevent further
clashes on the island and other disputed areas. 
</P>
