<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2110 GMT, October 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANTALYA (TURKEY) -- Yugoslav Foreign Minister Zivadin
Jovanovic said here Sunday that Belgrade opposes any form of
military intervention by foreign powers.
</P>
<P>
Emerging from his meeting with his Turkish counterpart Ismail
Cem, Jovanovic told Xinhua that the Kosovo issue is a completely
internal affair of the Yugoslav Federation and should be solved
under the principles of the U.N. Charter.
</P>
<P>
Jovanovic said the Balkan summit, which will open Monday
morning in southern Turkey's port city of Antalya, is of great
importance for peace and security in the region and Yugoslavia
hopes that the meeting will make a contribution to the settlement
of the Kosovo crisis. (Turkey-Yugoslav FM)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cypriot President Glafcos Clerides said Sunday that
the Greek Cypriot side is ready to discuss as a prior issue the
reduction of armaments on the island.
</P>
<P>
Clerides made the remark in a speech at the 18th annual march
of the refugees from the Turkish controlled north of the island.
</P>
<P>
"We will do everything possible to find a solution within the
framework of the U.N. decisions and resolutions," which provide
for a bizonal, bicommunal federation on the island, he said.
(Cyprus-Reducing Armaments)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
