<HEADLINE> Foreign Experts Receive Chime Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Eight foreign experts from
Germany, the United States. Japan, Denmark and Australia received
Chime awards from the government of central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Vice Governor Zhang Hongxiang attended the awards ceremony and
noted that the over 7,000 foreign experts who work in Hubei each
year represent an important technical and management contingent
promoting the province's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Today's event marked the fifth time Hubei has recognized
foreign experts for outstanding contributions. Some 44 foreign
experts have won the Chime Award.  
</P>
</TEXT>
