<HEADLINE> Fry Set for Release in Lijiang River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Some 50,000 fry will be released
into Lijiang River which flows through the popular scenic city of
Guilin in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The fry will be released between October 14-18 as part of an
effort to restore the ecological balance in the Lijiang River.
</P>
<P>
Some 144 fish species formerly thrived in the Lijiang. Today,
however, excessive fishing has the number to only 10 ten species.
</P>
<P>
The city's Tourism Commission has announced that thousands of
fry will henceforth be released in Lijiang on annual basis.
</P>
</TEXT>
