<HEADLINE> Somali Factions Quarrel Over Tariff  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 12 (Xinhua)-- Quarrels over port tariffs
and security arrangements escalated at the coastal areas in
ferries started docking into the sea ports controlled by Somali
faction leaders.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the Southern port town of Kismaio, 500 Km south
of Mogadishu, said Monday that a serious dispute has erupted between
Mohamed Saeed Hirsi Morgan and the business community in the town
over taxes imposed on the commercial goods. Morgan's
administration has increased the levy on the imported goods for
more than 20 percent in an attempt to compensate what is called
the various needs of the region,
</P>
<P>
According to the officials of General Morgan, the taxes are
increased so as to improve the security situation of the region
which has been deteriorating since last month. However, the
businessmen have rejected to pay such high taxes after expressing
their concern that the high levy will make the poor people of the
town incapable of buying their commodities.
</P>
<P>
The increase of the levies by Morgan's Majerten Clan has
obviously been prompted by the deployment of hundreds of heavily
armed militiamen and dozens of battle wagons in Middle Jubba
Region by their rival Marehan clan militiamen who had been
defeated and ousted from Kismaic and its surrounding areas in a
series of battles early in the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
