<HEADLINE> OAU to Focus on Refugee in Peace Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of
African Unity (OAU) has decided to focus on returnee, refugee and
internally displaced women and children for peace and development
drive on the continent, a senior OAU official said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
OAU Assistant Secretary General Ahmed Haggag said that as
economic integration can be achieved only in an environment of
peace, peace can be sustainable when reconstruction,
rehabilitation and reintegration are successfully completed in
former areas of conflict.
</P>
<P>
Haggag made the remarks at the opening ceremony of the regional
seminar on enhancing the participation of returnee, refugee and
internally displaced women and children in reconstruction,
rehabilitation and peace building.
</P>
<P>
He noted, "In Africa, over 20 million people are
currently living within the borders of their own countries,
internally displaced from their surroundings, deprived of their
livelihoods, dignity and hope."
</P>
<P>
"Women and children form the majority of refugee and displaced
population of any country during and after conflict," He added.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the four-day seminar to come up with a plan of action,
which "will constitute proposals for concrete and implementable
programs and activities for facilitating the reintegration of
vulnerable and marginalized groups in the development process and
resettlement in countries emerging from conflicts."  
</P>
</TEXT>
