<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Launches Railway Safety Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Railway (BR) Monday
launched a safety week in the capital city of Dhaka and elsewhere
across the country.
</P>
<P>
Six task forces in the western zone and four task forces in the
eastern zone will continuously monitor "safety and schedules" as
well as passengers' needs, the official BSS news agency quoted BR
officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
All passengers have been asked to report any travel hazard or
any specific need to the officials of the task forces during the
week.
</P>
<P>
The task forces will also evaluate the state of safety of
movements of trains and sustainability of the repaired tracks
which were damaged during the recent severe floods.
</P>
<P>
Other programs of the week include improvement of the passenger
services, strict adherence to emergency safety rules.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh has 4,364 kilometers of broad- and meter-gauge
railway line across the country covering an area of 148,393 square
kilometers. 
