derived their legality for their military intervention against
Yugoslavia from relevant U.N. Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
The official quoted U.N. Security Council Resolution 1199 as
saying that the Kosovo crisis not only affected domestic security
but also regional security as well, which, combined with
international human rights conventions, formed the legal basis for
the NATO action, he said.  (NATO-Air Strike-Yugoslavia)
</P>
