two years, Libregts will get a salary of 30,000 U.S. dollars per
month plus a one-off signing fee of 150,000 U.S. dollars in
addition to allowances for travel and housing.
</P>
<P>
As the sixth foreign coach to handle Nigeria in six years, his
immediate task is to raise a team to qualify for the Africa
Nations' Cup to be held in Zimbabwe in 2000.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria was ousted of the France World Cup when they were
trounced by Denmark 4-1 in the second round.
</P>
<P>
Former coach Bora Milutinovic's contract ended with the World
Cup in July. 
