<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Confers with Angolan President (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 12 (Xinhua) -- China is ready and willing to
join Angola is building stable equal, mutually beneficial and
sincere relations geared to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin made the remark during his talks with his
Angolan counterpart Jose Eduardo Dos Santos here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China values its traditional friendship with
Angola and considers the country a trusted friend.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have expanded friendly cooperation in
wide-ranging areas since President Dos Santos visited China in
1988, said Jiang, adding that the current visit will undoubtedly
deepen mutual understanding and advance bilateral relations in the
new world situation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed appreciations and gratitude for the Angolan
government's support of the "one China" policy and its six
successive years of support for China in the U.N. Human Rights
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Dos Santos said the goal of his current visit is to further
strengthen relations between Angola and China.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciation for China's economic achievements and
political stability, and said Angola should learn from China's
experience in related areas.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government will continue to support China's
position on human rights and the Taiwan issue, Dos Santos said. He
also voiced his hope that the foreign ministries of the two
nations will expand consultation and strengthen cooperation
related to global and regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
In terms of bilateral trade ties, Jiang said that the trade
volume between China and Angola has increased marginally over
recent years and acknowledged that Angola has emerged as China's
second largest trade partner in southern Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
