organizing committee promised Monday that the main games venues
would remain as planned in spite of some worries about delays in
construction amid the economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Charouck Arirachakaran, secretary general of the organizing
committee, made the remarks as he was here to promote the
upcoming Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
The secretary general said all facilities at the Bangkok
B-Land Sports Complex would be completed on time.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that construction of the B-Land complex had
been delayed and some of the seven sports to be staged there
might be relocated to the northern city of Chiang Mai.
</P>
<P>
