the northeast ridge, the Nepali Ministry of Tourism and Civil
Aviation said in press release Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ayumi Nozawai and Hirosi Iwazaki started at three in the
morning at Camp II (5,800m) and ascended the summit at 12:19 in
