Nepal including the 8,848-meter Mt. Qomolangma, the highest peak
in the world, during the Autumn season which began on September 1
and ends on November 15.
</P>
<P>
One of the teams abandoned bid on September 14 on the
8,163-meter Mt. Manaslu, the world's eighth highest mountain.
