<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industry on the Fast Track </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 12 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial growth rate
for September hit 10.2 percent, up 2.3 percentage points on the
August level, according to the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau predicted that the figure will rise even more in the
fourth quarter of the year in line with new government policies to
increase investment and expand domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the incremental industrial output ended
September at 172.9 billion yuan. The industrial sector's
January-September value-added output stood at 1,439.2 billion
yuan, up eight percent on the same period last year and 0.2
percentage points higher than the this year's January-August
period.
</P>
<P>
The bureau attributed industrial growth to government policies
designed to increase investments in infrastructure construction and
reconstruction in the wake of devastating summer flooding.
</P>
<P>
Various other favorable factors for the industrial sector
include the rapid growth of large enterprises and the booming
telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
The bureau reported that industrial sectors in most Chinese
municipalities, provinces and autonomous regions witnessed rapid
growth during September, with both state and non-state sectors
enjoying improved operations. State firms registered a September
growth rate of 5.8 percent, up 2.7 percentage points on August.
</P>
<P>
The sales/production ratio for the month grew by 0.9 percentage
points to 97.84 percent on an annual basis, according to the
bureau.  
</P>
</TEXT>
