<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Stronger as Buying Continues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar soared
one U.S. cent Monday, propelled by aggressive buying from overseas
hedge funds.
</P>
<P>
According to portfolio manager at Perpetual Funds Management,
Glen Howard, the funds were most likely still buying to cover
short positions, or feeling very bullish towards the local
currency.
</P>
<P>
It ended the day at 62.58 U.S. cents from Friday's close of
61.58, after trading between 61.32 and 62.85 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
