said the Australian dollar's strength was not altogether a
straightforward currency play but a U.S. buyer had made a
significant impact on the day.
</P>
<P>
"It was a very large chunk," he said and fueled the rally in a
short market.
</P>
<P>
He said the Australian dollar was also helped by further
weakness in the U.S. dollar as the Japanese market came on board.
</P>
<P>
The local currency was buying 72.63 Japanese yen from 71.47 and
1.0274 German marks from 1.0038. 
