<HEADLINE> Bodies of 3 Iranian Diplomats Identified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced Monday that the
three bodies returned by the Afghan Taliban have been identified
as those of Iranian diplomats killed by the group.
</P>
<P>
Mahmoud Amouei, head of Iran's delegation to receive the
bodies returned by the Taliban, told the official news agency IRNA
that the victims were identified as Mohammad Nasser Nasseri, Karim
Heidarian and Majid Nouri Niaraki.
</P>
<P>
The bodies were brought back Sunday to Mashhad, northeastern
province of Khorasan, by the International Committee of Red
Cross. They will be carried to Tehran for a funeral process on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Amouei said a four-hour study has found that the diplomats had
been displaced several times and that bullet wounds were all over
the bodies.
</P>
<P>
The three diplomats, alongside six others and an IRNA reporter,
were killed by the Taliban last August in northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the other seven Iranians were brought back to
Iran last month. 
