<HEADLINE> Symposium to Boost Beijing, HK Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Beijing/Hong Kong Economic
Cooperation Symposium, a three-day business event aimed at
promoting economic ties between the capital and Hong Kong, opened
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Mao, vice-mayor of Beijing, addressed the opening
ceremony. "After Hong Kong's return to the motherland, the ties
between these two cities have become closer with the areas of
cooperation widened," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
The official expressed the confidence that the close
relationship would be maintained and further advanced in spite of
new challenges and difficulties brought about by the regional
financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Zhang led a large trade delegation to Hong Kong, and brought
with him over 500 projects.
</P>
<P>
Yi Xiqun, assistant mayor of Beijing, told the gathering that
in the fields of high-tech industries, service industries and
enterprise restructuring, Beijing and Hong Kong are highly
complementary, and the potential of their cooperation is
tremendous.
</P>
<P>
His view was shared by Hong Kong's Acting Financial Secretary
Rafael Hui, who suggested that the two cities strengthen their
collaboration in tourism, real estate, finance and innovative
technology.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics from the Hong Kong Trade Development
Council, Hong Kong is the largest investor in Beijing. At present
 the number of Hong Kong-financed enterprises in Beijing has
topped 5,000, accounting for 40 percent of the total number of
foreign-funded enterprises in Beijing, and the contractual
investment has reached 10.7 billion U.S. dollars or 48 percent of
the total.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is organized by the Beijing municipal
government, the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
government and major Hong Kong business chambers. It comprises of
plenary sessions, seminars, business discussion, photo display
and contract signing ceremony. 
