<HEADLINE> More Goods Handled at Macao Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The amount of freight transport
at the Macao International Airport in the first nine months of the
year exceeded that of the entire year of 1997, according to
figures from the airport.
</P>
<P>
From January to September, the airport handled 45,664 tons of
goods, up 52 percent over the same period last year and
surpassing the total amount of 45,540 tons handled for all of 1997.
</P>
<P>
On average, monthly freight transport in 1997 was about 4,000
tons. In comparison, the airport handled 10,412 tons of goods in
July this year due to unsuccessful operation at the Chek Lap Kok
Airport of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In August and September when the operation of the Hong Kong
airport became normal, the monthly cargo handling capacity at the
Macao airport surpassed 5,500 tons.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Macao International Airport handled more than
1.64 million passengers during the first nine months of the year,
an increase of 11 percent over that of last year.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 11 airline companies are using the airport. Every
week, some 400 flights shuttle between Macao and 26 cities, 14 of
which are in China's mainland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
