<HEADLINE> Int'l Conference on Renewable Energy Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Representatives from 23
countries began here Monday a meeting on the role of renewable
energy technology for rural development.
</P>
<P>
A total of 68 papers are scheduled to be presented at the
three-day conference attended by countries in Asia, Africa,
Europe, North America and Oceania.
</P>
<P>
The conference aims to disseminate successful renewable energy
technology (RET) undertaken in the participating countries,
exchange experiences and information, maintain closer cooperation
among the participating countries and explore the existing
engineering educational activities related to RET, said a press
release issued on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
The conference is being organized jointly by the Alternative
Energy Promotion Center under the Nepali Ministry of Science and
Technology, the Institute of Engineering of Nepal's Tribhuvan
University and the Nepal Solar Energy Society.
</P>
<P>
In Nepal, there are gaps and bottlenecks to optimize the use of
RET for the benefit of rural people, and the limited knowledge in
the area of technology, policy and program at implementation level
is the major reason of unsuccessful results in some RET-related
cases, the press release said. 
