<HEADLINE> Brownout Hits Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- A wide area of Luzon, one of the
three largest islands in the Philippines, and portions of Metro
Manila were hit by a brownout starting at 10 a.m. Monday.
</P>
<P>
The National Power Corporation (Napocor) said the brownout was
triggered by a trip-off at a power plant outside Manila, causing
the overloading of powerlines.
</P>
<P>
Affected areas are Southern and Eastern Luzon. As of 1 p.m.
Monday Napocor had restored 20 percent of the affected areas
including Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Complete restoration is expected at 5 p.m. Monday, Napocor
said. It added that other areas in Luzon suffered low voltage
which prompted the power firm to interrupt the normal flow of
electricity. 
