<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills 15, Injures 21 in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people were killed and
21 others injured when a bus collided with a lorry in southern
Iran Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The bus was on its way to the southwestern province Khuzestan
from central province Isfahan when the accident took place on the
Isfahan-Khuzestan road, 30 kilometers away from Khoramabad, the
provincial capital of Lorestan, official news agency IRNA reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Both drivers and 13 passengers were killed instantly, police
sources were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to Khoramabad hospital for treatment
but some of them were reported to be in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Investigations are underway to find out the reason for the
accident, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
