<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 979 Die of Gastroenteritis, Encephalitis in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 12 (Xinhua) -- A total of 979 people have
died of gastroenteritis and encephalitis since mid-April in Nepal,
the Health Ministry said in a press release Monday.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 840 people have succumbed to gastroenteritis in 45
of the 75 districts in the country and 51,550 others have been
affected by the disease, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
It said that most of the patients were children aged between
three and five.
</P>
<P>
The disease used to be under control before mid-September in
the past years, but this year it is still raging in the country
after that time and the number of deaths from the disease has
increased over the previous years, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
During the last three years, a total of 477,419 people suffered
from gastroenteritis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 139 people have died of encephalitis this year and
981 others have been affected, the ministry added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
