<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Cuts Short Visit to Central Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Monday cut short his trip to Central Asia and was returning to
Moscow, Russian news agencies said.
</P>
<P>
The agencies gave no reason for the change in plans.
</P>
<P>
The president is suffering from a cold.
</P>
<P>
The North Atlantic Treaty Organization was meeting on Monday to
authorize airstrikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Russia has been strongly opposed to any military actions
against Yugoslavia over the Kosovo crisis. 
