<HEADLINE> Official: Yeltsin Recovering From Cold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin, now on a visit to Uzbekistan, is recovering from a cold
he caught Sunday, his press secretary Dmitry Yakushkin said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin is feeling better now, Yakushkin was quoted as saying
by an Interfax dispatch from Tashkent, the Uzbek capital.
</P>
<P>
The improved condition, the Interfax report said, has been
confirmed by Sergei Mironov, director general of the medical
center in the presidential administration.
</P>
<P>
"Yeltsin's cold will not affect the program of his state visits
to Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan" on October 11-13, Yakushkin said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin appeared stiff and stumbled Sunday when he arrived in
Tashkent and had to cancel his other public events of the day.
</P>
