<HEADLINE> China's Shandong Anticipates Record Autumn Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province, a
major grain producer, is expected to reap a record autumn grain
harvest this year, according to official estimates.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's autumn grain output is likely to reach a record high
22.5 billion kg this year, five billion kg more than last year,
according to Zheng Shoulong, deputy director of the provincial
agricultural department.
</P>
<P>
The increase in grain output alone is expected to raise the per
capita income of Shandong farmers by more than 100 yuan, Zheng
said.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that the province's autumn grain acreage
this year totaled four million hectares.
</P>
<P>
Last year Shandong's autumn grain harvest fell off by 2.5
billion kg due to severe drought and windstorms.  
</P>
</TEXT>
