<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda's Coffee Export Drops in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's coffee exports in
September this year dropped 40.6 percent to 207,931 bags compared
to 350,197 bags registered in the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Monday's Monitor daily quoted a monthly report of Uganda
Coffee Development Authority as saying that the plunge is due to
a reduction in the farm level production caused by heavy rains.
</P>
<P>
The report also said September is usually an off-season month
and volumes are minimal, adding that farmers are busy preparing
fro the beginning of the new season in the month.
</P>
<P>
In relation to the same period last year, September 1998
exports declined by 5.5 and 10 percents respectively in terms of
volume and value.
</P>
<P>
In the 1997/1998 coffee year ending September 30, Uganda
exported 3 million bags of coffee with a value of some 274
million U.S. Dollars, a decline of 29 percent in volume and 22.7
percent in value from the preceding year.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is Uganda's key export product and accounts for 60
percent of its total foreign exchange earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
