<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Govt Assures Actions Against Kidnappers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government
assured the public Monday that it has taken necessary steps to go
after kidnappers who preyed on wealthy businessmen, particularly
members of the Chinese Filipino community in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
Press Secretary Rodolfo Reyes said President Joseph Estrada has
ordered the Presidential Anti-Organized Crime Task Force to pound
hard against these criminals without jeopardizing the safety of
kidnap victims.
</P>
<P>
"Steps are already being taken. It seems we are being
challenged," Reyes said.
</P>
<P>
During the past few weeks, a number of kidnapping incidents
occurred in Manila and the southern Philippines, involving some
foreigners and local rich businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, National Adviser Alexander Aguirre said the
president has directed a caretaker committee tasked to closely
monitor the peace and order situation, especially the progress of
operations on the kidnapping incidents in Manila and the south.
</P>
<P>
He said regional monitoring centers, which report regularly to
the National Security Monitoring Center in the Presidential
Palace, have also been activated nationwide to keep a close watch
on the peace and order situation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
