<DOCNO> XIE19981012.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Drafts Long-Awaited Constitution Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 12 (Xinhua) -- A bill on the review of
Kenya's constitution, being drafted by Kenya's Attorney-General,
will be presented to parliament within a month, following a split
among groups charged with preparing it.
</P>
<P>
A dispute over the review process resulted in the National
Convention Executive Council (NCEC), the umbrella body of
opposition lobby groups during l997 pre-election campaigns,
leaving the 10-man constitutional drafting committee, the East
African weekly reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NCEC wanted a "multi-sectoral caucus" set up to advise on
a bill covering the appointment of commissioners to the Kenyan
Constitution Review Commission before it is debated in
parliament, said the report.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the Attorney-General's office was
preparing to publish th final bill for debate next month and the
drafting committee is expected to endorse the final amendments
within a fortnight.
</P>
<P>
"This is a fairly urgent bill and there is unanimity within
the drafting committee that the effort that has gone into the
process is more important than the NCEC's self-serving attitude,"
a state counsel on the drafting committee said.
</P>
<P>
The constitution review commission is expected to hear views
around the country on constitutional reform within two and a half
years and prepare a new constitution before the next general
elections, slated for December 2002.
</P>
<P>
The NCEC, however, said it believes that crucial issues
related to the time-frame for the constitutional review process
have not been addressed, arguing that this could impede the
commission's work.
</P>
<P>
Sources within the drafting committee alleged that the
fall-out between the NCEC and other committee members was
precipitated by the unwillingness of the latter to reserve a seat
for the lobby group on the review commission.
</P>
<P>
But the NCEC played down disagreements on automatic
representation within the commission, warning that its unilateral
withdrawal indicated its displeasure with the Attorney-General's
growing encroachment on the drafting committee's business.
</P>
<P>
"The Attorney-General has encroached on the committee's work,
which calls for reconstituting the committee to ensure the final
draft bill is sound and legitimate," argued Kibutha Kibwana, the
convener of the NCEC.
</P>
<P>
The constitution review was very highlighted during the
confrontations between the government and the opposition before
the country's second multi-party general elections held at the
end of December last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
