<HEADLINE> Chinese Tourism Industry Grows in January-August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 12 (Xinhua) -- China's overseas tourism
industry has not been influenced by the Asian financial crisis and
this summer's flooding, as the number of overseas tourists grew by
12.22 percent in the first eight months this year.
</P>
<P>
According to latest statistics from the China National Tourism
Administration (CNTA), the country hosted 41.33 million overseas
tourists in the eight months to August, with earnings rising 5.55
percent to 8.20 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The number of foreign tourists decreased 3.02 percent to 4.62
million and that of tourists from Hong Kong and Macao grew 19.3
percent to 35.17 million.
</P>
<P>
Among the 15 major tourist sources, the number of tourists from
Australian and Kazakhstan increased by more than 20 percent, while
that of tourists from Thailand dropped by 30.09 percent. The total
number of tourists from Asia as a whole went down by 8.02
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
