<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aliyev Reelected Azerbaijani President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Azerbaijani President Geidar
Aliyev was re-elected despite the boycott by opposition groups in
Sunday's election, the Interfax news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Aliyev, 75, pocketed 77 percent of the ballots cast at the
presidential election, well over the two-thirds needed for a win,
a Central Election Committee source was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
By law, this means a second round of voting is not needed.
</P>
<P>
The pitch among six pro-government candidates, including the
incumbent, drew some 74 percent of eligible voters to polling
stations, enough to make the election valid, the source said.
</P>
<P>
Aliyev was elected president of this Caspian oil-rich country
for the first time in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
