<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, October 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- The Indian Defense Ministry confirmed Sunday that
its army and air force were scheduled to stage a "formation-level"
exercise next month along its border with neighboring Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times daily reported Monday that the
brigade-level exercise was a "routine and a planned one" with the
participation of the Indian Air Force. Western observers were
reportedly alarmed at India's plan for the military maneuver with
100,000 troops on its border with its arch-enemy Pakistan.
(India-Military Exercise)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romanian Supreme National Defense Council
announced Sunday that Romania will grant access to its airspace to
NATO "in case of emergency."
</P>
<P>
The decision was made in response to a NATO request two days
ago asking Romania to provide air corridor for its possible
strikes against Yugoslavia, said Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu. (Romania-NATO-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke said Sunday that his
talks with Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic did not get any
progress.
</P>
<P>
Holbrooke met again Sunday with Milosevic, aiming to avert
possible NATO (North Atlantic Treaty Organization)
airstrikes. Before the new round of the talks, Holbrooke told
reporters that compared with the situation in Yugoslavia a few
days ago, there was nothing changed and the situation was still
very serious. (Yugoslavia-Holbrooke) 
</P>
