<HEADLINE> International Traffic Capacity Seminar Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 12 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar on
road traffic capacity was held recently in this capital of east
China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 80 road and bridge experts from China, the United
States, Germany, Sweden and a number of other countries and
regions attended the seminar organized by the Southeast China
University and a highway research institute of the Ministry of
Communications.
</P>
<P>
Traffic capacity research is a relatively new subject in
China. Chinese experts will take for reference the experiences of
other countries to make the country's handbook of road traffic
capacity, which is expected to come out next year.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that China had 1.25 million kilometers of
highways by the end of last year, including 4,700 kilometers of
expressways.  
</P>
