<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norwegian Company Bets on China's Market Potential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Norsk Hydroasa of Norway, a
major agricultural company, has vowed to increase its presence in
China where it sees a huge market potential, a company official
said here at a seminar on environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
"We will further our technical cooperation with China to
produce environment-friendly products with good economic returns,"
the official said.
</P>
<P>
China has managed to stay relatively stable during the Asian
financial crisis which erupted in July 1997 and ensnared a number
of Asian countries including Thailand, Indonesia and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1905, the Norwegian company specializes in
agriculture, petroleum, natural gas, light metals and
petrochemicals. It currently sells some 500,000 to 800,000 tons of
fertilizers to China each year, and has two production ventures in
Taicang in Jiangsu Province and Rizhao in Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The official said that his company is also considering producing
heat converters used in automobile air conditioning in Shanghai,
China's leading economic and financial center.  
</P>
</TEXT>
