<HEADLINE> Bodies of Remaining Diplomats Returned to Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The bodies of three other
Iranian diplomats killed by the Afghan Taliban militia have been
returned to Iran, the official news agency IRNA reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
A plane of the International Committee of the Red Cross carried
the bodies Sunday night to Mashhad in the northeastern province of
Khorasan.
</P>
<P>
The bodies will be identified in Mashhad before being
transferred to Tehran for a funeral procession on Friday, IRNA
said.
</P>
<P>
Taliban militia killed eight Iranian diplomats and an IRNA
reporter after the group captured Mazari Sharif, northern
Afghanistan, in August. Six bodies of the Iranian diplomats and
the reporter were transferred to Iran last month.
</P>
<P>
Angered by Taliban's atrocity, Iran has threatened retaliation
against the group and massed 200,000 troops on the Afghan border.
</P>
<P>
An Iranian Foreign Ministry official, speaking on condition of
anonymity, set conditions Sunday on a possible visit to Tehran by
Taliban officials, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
No Taliban members will be allowed to visit Tehran unless they
bring back the Iranian citizens kidnaped by the group, arrest and
punish those killing the Iranian diplomats and the reporter, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
A London-based Arabic weekly reported recently that a
representative of the Taliban group is to pay a visit to Tehran in
the coming days to start negotiations with Iranian officials.
</P>
<P>
Iran said Taliban has detained more than 40 Iranian drivers
and aid workers in Afghanistan. Ten Iranians were released in two
groups in the past two months.
</P>
<P>
Reports said Taliban decided Sunday to set free another 10
Iranians after a mediation of a Palestinian delegation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
