<HEADLINE> New Vehicle Sales Rise in New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand saw an increase
of 10 percent in new vehicle sales in September, the New Zealand
Press Association (NZPA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Total sales of new vehicles last month were 6,068, the second
highest figure recorded in the past 11 months. It represented an
increase of 577 over the August figure.
</P>
<P>
The increase in new vehicle sales was attributed to realigned
prices after the removal of tariffs on motor vehicles in the
country and a recognition that the New Zealand dollar was falling.
</P>
<P>
However, new vehicle sales for the first nine months of 1998
were well down on last year. A total of 48,214 new vehicles had
been sold, 11.6 percent down on the 54,586 sold during the first
nine months of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Toyota sold 1,210 new vehicles in September, accounting for
19.9 percent of the New Zealand market. 
</P>
