<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
closed higher here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 20 points higher at 1,724 with a
turnover of 48 million NZ dollars (25.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, AMP was the biggest winner, rising 10
cents to 2,185 cents, followed by Telecom and Carter Holt Harvey,
gaining 6 cents each to 738 and 130 cents respectively. Auckland
Airport and Fletcher Energy put on 5 cents each to 191 and 372
cents respectively, while Brierley Investments got 3 cents to 39
cents, Fletcher Forest 2 cents to 52 cents, and Fletcher Building
and Air New Zealand 1 cent each to 199 and 145 cents respectively.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Paper lost 3 cents to 95 cents. 
</P>
