<HEADLINE> Arts, Cultural Societies to Be Set up in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government is to
set up Arts and Cultural Societies in every Divisional Secretariat
area, according to the Ministry of Cultural Affairs sources Monday
</P>
<P>
The sources said already two societies have been set up at
Kegalle in North Western province and Dankotuwa in Sabargaviuwa
province, and About 50 such societies will be set up next year.
</P>
<P>
The main aim of the government in forming the societies is to
create an interest in the people in national arts and cultural
activities to promote arts and cultural development, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
They said that the members of the Arts and Cultural Societies
would formulate the basis for the policies and action programs
required to develop the arts and culture of the island nation.
</P>
<P>
The Sinhala, Tamil and Muslim cultural activities will be
stepped up and a very healthy rapport among them will be
established to build the basis for communal harmony, peace and
development, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
