<HEADLINE> Myanmar Chamber of Commerce Signs 12 MOUs With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 12 (Xinhua) -- The Union of Myanmar Chamber of
Commerce and Industry (UMCCI), a major trade organization of its
kind in the country, has signed 12 memorandums of understanding
(MOUs) with its counterparts from nine countries since May 1989,
seeking economic cooperation with them.
</P>
<P>
According to the recent issue of the Myanmar Business News
published by UMCCI, these foreign chambers of commerce include
four from Japan, two from Bangladesh and one each from Germany,
Israel, South Korea, Nepal, Singapore and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
There are 35 different chambers of commerce in Myanmar now.
</P>
<P>
Private enterprises operating in Myanmar numbered 25,151 at the
end of June this year, of which exporters and importers were
9,250, business representatives 2,092, partnership firms 1,218,
Myanmar companies 11,214, foreign companies and branches 1,219,
Myanmar-foreign joint ventures 123 and chambers of commerce 35.
</P>
