<HEADLINE> Profession of Lawyer Attracts Young, Educated People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Participants in the two-day
national lawyer qualification examination, that concluded yesterday,
are younger and have higher educational backgrounds, today's China
Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted statistics released by the Ministry of Justice
as saying that 71.4 percent of the exam participants were under
the age of 30.
</P>
<P>
About 60 to 70 percent of those registered for the exam had
received a formal law education. More than one-third of those
registered in Beijing and Shanghai have completed four years of
law education in colleges.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, more civil servants took the
exams. Officials working in Party and governmental departments
accounted for 26.17 percent, ranking first of all categories.
</P>
<P>
Ministry officials said that this was due to the proposed
reduction of the number of government employees.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, local governments at all levels will
start downsizing next year in order to increase efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Qualification exams are becoming more popular in China, not
only for lawyers but also for accountants, real estate appraisers
and physicians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
