<HEADLINE> Dalian in Northeast China Issues Bonds Nationwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 12 (Xinhua) -- A construction investment
company in Dalian, a coastal open city in northeast China's
Liaoning Province, has begun issuing 180 million yuan worth of
bonds in seven cities throughout the country, the first time a
local company has issued bonds nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The money raised from these sales will be used for a project to
divert the Biliuhe River more than 100 km away in the northeast
into the city, and this work is expected to be completed by the
end of 1999.
