<HEADLINE> China Appraises Automatic Power-Distributing System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 12 (Xinhua) -- An automatic
power-distributing system for urban grids which has successfully
operated for over one year in Handan in north China's Hebei
Province has been appraised by the China Power Company.
</P>
<P>
Armed with computer network technology, the system has helped
the city increase the reliability of its power supply to 99.93
percent and decrease wear and tear on the distribution network by
three percent.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the advanced and multi-functional system now
operates at a world-standard level.
</P>
<P>
Since the city introduced the system, it has raised its power
supply by 2,032 kwh annually and added more than 200 million yuan
to the industrial output value.
</P>
<P>
The system is expected to give an impetus to the improvement
of urban electric grids throughout the country.  
</P>
