<HEADLINE> Thailand Deports 270,000 Illegal Foreign Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 12 (Xinhua) -- More than 270,000 illegal
foreign workers have been deported by the Thai government since
January as part of the government policy to replace alien workers
with Thais, the Bangkok Post reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Immigration Bureau commissioner Chidchai Wannasathit was quoted
as saying that the bureau has so far deported 271,019 illegal
foreign workers and arrested 34 people for smuggling foreigners
into the country.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he said 111 others have been arrested for housing
foreign workers since January this year.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has also established a unit to suppress
international crimes, particularly forgery of immigration
documents, the flesh trade and Mafia-type activities, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said his agency has also drawn up careful security plans to
the December 6-20 Asian Games to be held in Bangkok and other
provinces. 
</P>
