<HEADLINE> Davenport Upset by Testud in WTA Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Sandrine Testud of France
Sunday upset the newly-crowned world number one Lindsay Davenport
of the United States 7-5, 6-3 in the final of the WTA event in
Filderstadt.
</P>
<P>
The 18th-ranked Testud came back from 5-4 down in the first
set to take the next three games and the set.
</P>
<P>
The French player went on to go 3-1 up in the second set and
then held her serve to take the set 6-3. 
