<HEADLINE> Gascoigne in Clinic over Alcohol Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 11 (Xinhua) -- English Premier club
Middlesbrough admitted on Sunday that Paul Gascoigne spent the
weekend in a specialist clinic.
</P>
<P>
The England midfielder checked into the clinic last week after
the latest in a series of high profile drink-related incidents.
</P>
<P>
The announcement follows Saturday's confirmation from manager
Bryan Robson that Gascoigne is suffering from stress and alcohol
problems.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough spokesman Dave Allan said: "Bryan Robson regards
him as a friend as well as a player. Everyone at the football
club wants to do their best for Gascoigne.
</P>
<P>
"Gascoigne will remain away from the club while the clinic
staff consider his symptoms. The club will be guided by their
advice over his welfare."
</P>
<P>
Robson's revelation that Gascoigne was in trouble followed
newspaper reports which claimed the player returned from a trip
to the Republic of Ireland with a facial injury after falling
over while drunk.
</P>
<P>
"Gazza has got a problem. It's been building up for quite a
few years. Everybody keeps talking about the drink and it's a
little bit of that because he does get down at times," said
Robson.
</P>
<P>
"People talk about stress in football and Gazza, in all the
years I've been in football, has had more of a high profile than
anybody I've ever known."
</P>
<P>
Gascoigne joined Middlesbrough from Glasgow Rangers late last
season and played a part as they won promotion back to the FA
Premier League.
</P>
<P>
But problems have mounted this year with divorce from his
wife, the death of a friend and his omission from England's 22
for the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Paul Merson, a recovering alcoholic, left Middlesbrough for
Aston Villa earlier this season after claiming that a culture of
drinking at the club was too much of a temptation to him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
