<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 11 (Xinhua) -- English Premier club Newcastle
United is involved in 150 million pound (256.7 million U.S.
dollars) takeover talks with a media-based company, according to
local reports on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Mail On Sunday said negotiations were at an advanced stage
and that "the conviction now on Tyneside is that a deal to buy
control of Newcastle from Douglas Hall, who owns a majority
stake, is imminent".
</P>
<P>
Speculation has been rife that Newcastle and other quoted
clubs are heading for takeover bids ever since satellite
broadcaster BSkyB made its billion dollar bid last month for top
club Manchester United.
</P>
<P>
Recent reports have suggested a variety of companies are
interested in Newcastle, including Cable &AMP; Wireless
Communications Plc and TeleWest Communications Plc.
</P>
<P>
