<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Bridge Construction Proceeds Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a new bridge
spanning the Yangtze River in Wuhu, east China's Anhui Province,
has proceeded smoothly in spite of devastating summer flooding.
</P>
<P>
The Wuhu Yangtze River Bridge, the largest structure of its
kind in China, includes a railway bridge some 10,616 meters in
length and a highway bridge stretching 6,078 meters.
</P>
<P>
The bridge's 312-meter main span will be the longest for any
similar structure in China.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the project commenced on March 22, 1997, and is
scheduled for completion in September 2000. About a quarter of the
4.5 billion yuan investment has been materialized so far.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
