<HEADLINE> Kenyans Sweep Chicago Marathon Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Ondoro Osoro, who had never
run a marathon before, led a Kenya's title sweep in Chicago
Marathon race Sunday and registered the third fastest time in
history in 2 hours,6 minutes and 54 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Osoro, a former cross-country runner, finished the race 49
seconds outside the world best time set by Ronaldo Da Costa at
last month's Berlin Marathon.
</P>
<P>
Joyce Chepchumba, London Marathon winner last year, grabbed
the women's title for Kenya with a personal best of 2:23:57.
</P>
<P>
"It was my first marathon and I think I'm very happy," Osoro
said. "I must be a lucky man today, running for the first time
and running very well."
</P>
<P>
Osoco didn't surge to the leading position until the last mile
where he rolled over Moroccan defending champion Khalid
Khannouchi.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan missed competitions for almost two years after a
car accident in 1995. He set records for debut, and broke the
course record of 2:07:10, set by Khannouchi last year.
</P>
<P>
Khannouchi finished second at 2:07.19 ahead of Gert Thys of
South Africa, 2:07.43.
</P>
<P>
In the women's section, South Africans De Reuck finished
second at 2:27:04 and Elana Meyer was third at 2:27:20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
