<HEADLINE> Liaoning Anticipates Record Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 12 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Province, a heavy
industrial base in northeast China, expects to produce 17.5
billion kg of grain this year, according to the provincial
agricultural bureau.
</P>
<P>
The projected output will surpass the 1993 record by some 500
million kg.
</P>
<P>
The anticipated good harvest in spite of difficulties caused by
bad weather has been attributed to increased funding which has
improved production conditions.
</P>
<P>
Other factors for the expected harvest include reform of
traditional farming methods, the promotion of practical agronomic
techniques, the use of new crop varieties and expanded training
for farmers.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government allocated 2.11 billion yuan to build
a number of irrigation facilities for spring planting this year
when there was a severe drought.
</P>
<P>
Some 4.91 million farmers have participated in various
agronomic training courses since last winter, laying a solid
foundation for the further development of agriculture in the
province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
